title: Sutton v Arsenal squad comparison ahead of fifth round FA Cup tie at Gander Green Lane
text:
Sutton v Arsenal squad comparison ahead of fifth round FA Cup tie at Gander Green Lane The Gunners and the Yellows' most recent line-ups are compared for cost and international experience Share Arsenal and Sutton's squads are compared ahead of tonight's cup tie (Photo: Getty Images / Rex Features) Share Get daily updates directly to your inbox + Subscribe Thank you for subscribing! Giant-killers Sutton will play Premier League side Arsenal on Monday in the most eye-catching FA Cup fifth-round tie. 
The hosts, 17th in the Vanarama National League, are 105 places below the 12-time FA Cup winners and are playing at this stage of the competition for the first time, though they beat Sky Bet Championship side Leeds to get here. 
The pressure is on the Gunners and defeat would surely intensify it to a level where Arsene Wenger would struggle to stay beyond this term. 
Here, Press Association Sport's Thomas England compares the two teams' most recent line-ups in terms of cost and international experience. Gander Green Lane will play host to Sutton vs Arsenal (Photo: Ian Walton) Sutton 
Signed: Free transfer, AFC Wimbledon 
Nationality: English
